Fond memories from when this place was O'Connors prompted me to try the lunch special.  The bartender I got was a nice guy, and the place is decent.  But the other bartender seemed to think it was Ok to have a loud conversation in a quiet bar about how "if Trump runs again, he'll win, because we're not stupid and we're not racist. We knew exactly what we were getting with Trump."  So, if you bartend at a bar in Park Slope and go on a pro-Trump rant in your bar *you are* stupid - at business, if for nothing else.  The continued diatribe about how celebrities shouldn't use their platform for political purposes is equally stupid. Everyone has free speech, but that doesn't protect anyone from the consequences of their speech (see: this review, for example.) I mean, you're literally standing behind a bar with an audience of your own, spouting your own political beliefs.... which are basically that you don't want people saying what they think in public.  I might be back. The bar is OK, and I can't imagine the management doesn't understand why patrons don't want their values belittled while they're enjoying a passable roast beef au jus.  As I was leaving I saw the guy staring into space with his hands in his pockets, while the bartender who served me was doing the lion's share of the bar work.
